be unhappy with the situation and decide instead of doing the right thing and communicating this with

92
00:06:42.070 --> 00:06:46.610
you they decide to just disappear hoping you just go away.

93
00:06:46.840 --> 00:06:52.390
Are three their business runs out of money and they need to close down operations and quickly cut costs

94
00:06:52.690 --> 00:06:55.730
and they decide to not share this with you.

95
00:06:55.760 --> 00:07:00.860
It is surprising how often number three happens a lot of clients do not contact you back because they

96
00:07:00.860 --> 00:07:05.540
no longer need your services in the middle of a project and they have no money to pay you for your work

97
00:07:05.540 --> 00:07:12.770
so far so ghosting you are disappearing is their way of solving the issue number two and three are just

98
00:07:12.770 --> 00:07:13.580
not right.

99
00:07:13.580 --> 00:07:18.800
And I found this out by trying to hunt down clients who have not paid before and realize those were

100
00:07:18.800 --> 00:07:21.230
the situations they were in.

101
00:07:21.290 --> 00:07:26.840
First of all this is another reason why having a contract with an upfront non-refundable deposit is

102
00:07:26.840 --> 00:07:27.740
helpful.

103
00:07:27.740 --> 00:07:33.920
At least you get to keep some money before they disappeared secondly if you did not have a contract

104
00:07:33.980 --> 00:07:36.520
or it was the project was too small to need one.

105
00:07:36.710 --> 00:07:40.620
You have to admit something to yourself you cannot help the situation.

106
00:07:40.640 --> 00:07:41.550
It happens.

107
00:07:41.630 --> 00:07:47.130
You could spend hours tracking these clients down and sending them spiteful emails until they pay.

108
00:07:47.210 --> 00:07:50.060
But there's a good chance they never will at this point.

109
00:07:50.240 --> 00:07:56.580
And it's better for you to focus your energy on a new client I have wasted many hours trying to reclaim

110
00:07:56.580 --> 00:07:57.580
lost money.

111
00:07:57.660 --> 00:08:02.640
If the project is large enough and you've already completed thousands of dollars of work you could hire

112
00:08:02.640 --> 00:08:06.180
a debt collector or sue them in small claims court.

113
00:08:06.180 --> 00:08:11.730
But even those activities end up costing you so much money and time it would only be worth pursuing

114
00:08:11.730 --> 00:08:14.420
